We have very good debugging tools, to be  honest. One [improvement] could be a standardized way of  putting some more source level debugging information in the  logs (Subject 8). The practical limitations of adding more  information to log files are obvious, in an ideal world, youd  have the stack trace for every line that was written to the log  because you never know what youre going to need. But, of  course, theres going to be a lot of overhead (Subject 15).
